<br>
However, the portion about Luclin teleports or druid abilities to tranport players around in Luclin is not appropriate for this petition. Here is the reason. The Luclin expansion in unique for EQ. For the first time, any player class or race can travel to the Nexus, Shadowhaven, and surrounding zones without initially being KOS. In other words, good and evil races and classes exist side by side in this expansion. (It's not that way in the Old World or in Kunark or Velious.) At the same time, all players have the same travel restrictions placed on them - we all get to run through all of the zones in Luclin. In Verant's words, there is content in these zones that they don't want players to pass over. (Remember, it was that way when Velious came out and dragon ring keys were required to be ported to Great Divide, Wakening Land, or Cobalt Scar.) <br>
<br>
Asking for druid ports on Luclin only cheapens the whole petition. It does not belong with the other concerns. For that reason, I cannot support the petition in its present form<br>
<br>
Rolaque<br>
